15:
Wretch... You— *cough*
You should have DIED... long ago!
25:
Your Highness, we've no intentions on 
your life, I assure you.
30: You think I'll believe that? Now?
33:
We mean no harm to you or your 
subjects. This is precisely why we 
stand before you, asking for a truce! 
Let there be peace!
35: Sir Albert, if you would be so kind.
39:
Very well. You can keep your throne.
However, I shall assume full command 
over the upcoming peace negotiations.
43:
For the prosperity of your people, and 
for your long and continued rule, there 
must be peace. 
What say you, Your Highness?
47:
...The catfolk shan't be so quick to 
forget that day, twenty odd years ago. 
The prince speaks of peace now! 
But for how much longer?!
53:
Their king died tryin' to end the war. 
Honor his wishes, and the catfolk'll 
probably forgive you.
56:
Now sit your ass in that fancy chair 
and cooperate, got it?
61:
...I appoint Albert as my regent, and... 
And bequeath unto him all command 
over peace negotiations with the 
catfolk.
64: Albert's done it! He's gone and done it!
66: Yes, with your aid. Thank you.
73:
Nimbuuus! You did it, man!
You were so cool! That was AWESOME!
75:
Man, you gave me goosebumps at the 
end there.
78:
Run your mouth all you want. 
I'm not fallin' for it.
85:
Either way, we owe you, dude. Peace 
talks are a go, no one got hurt, and Al 
avoided a trip to the dungeons. 
So yeah! Life is good.
88:
Nimbus. Light, Stella, and Alk. Allow me 
to extend each of you my deepest 
gratitude. With this, the dog and 
catfolk are saved!
90:
Could we ask you to lend us your aid 
but a little longer?
98:
To go tell the rest of the catfolk! Now 
Al's in charge of negotiations, we've 
just gotta get him to the village and 
work out a treaty.
100:
Then, at long, long, looong long last... 
the war will be officially over!
